Sentencas: Anode-supported proton conducting micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SOFCs) with the configuration of Ni-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY)/BZCY/BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta (BZY)/La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)-BZY have been prepared by a combination of phase inversion method and suspension-coating technique.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of stable micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells with BZCY-BZY bi-layer proton conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: The obtained Ni-BZCY anode hollow fiber presents a special asymmetrical structure consisting of a sponge-like layer and a finger-like porous layer, which is propitious to anode electrochemical process.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of stable micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells with BZCY-BZY bi-layer proton conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: Bi-layer electrolytes consisting of 5 mu m thick BZCY and 3 mu m thick BZY are successfully fabricated by suspension-coating technique.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of stable micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells with BZCY-BZY bi-layer proton conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: BZY electrolytes are placed at the cathode side, in order to improve the chemical stability against CO2.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of stable micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells with BZCY-BZY bi-layer proton conducting electrolytes

Sentencas: The considerable electrochemical performance and good stability in the presence of CO2 indicate that the construction of BZY-BZCY bilayer electrolytes is an effective way for the development of stable proton conducting MTSOFCs.
Titulo: Fabrication and evaluation of stable micro tubular solid oxide fuel cells with BZCY-BZY bi-layer proton conducting electrolytes
